<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10030] Throw exception while fetching a key from a single partition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10030</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;StreamThreadStateStoreProvider#stores throws exception&#160;whenever taskId is not found, which is not correct behaviour in multi-threaded env where state store partitions are distributed among several StreamTasks.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Task task = tasks.get(keyTaskId);
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (task == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InvalidStateStoreException(
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;The specified partition %d &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; store %s does not exist.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
 storeQueryParams.partition(),
 storeName));
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reproducible with KStream number of threads more then 1&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;StoreQueryIntegrationTest#streamsConfiguration&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;config.put(StreamsConfig.NUM_STREAM_THREADS_CONFIG, 2);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggested solution is to not throw exception if at least one state store is found&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>StreamsConfig.NUM_STREAM_THREADS_CONFIG=2</environment>
